Strong Quake Hits Mexico and Guatemala
A strong earthquake rocked southern Mexico and Guatemala early Monday, reportedly killing four people and causing damage across the region.
The 6.9 magnitude quake struck at 6:23 a.m. local time on the Mexican Pacific coast near the border with Guatemala, around 47 kilometers (29 miles) southwest of the city of Tapachula, according to the Mexican Seismological Service. The U.S. Geological Survey initially reported the quake at magnitude 7.1, and then lowered it to 6.9.